name: r-ggrastr
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "1.0.1" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-ggrastr
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/ggrastr_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/ggrastr/ggrastr_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 82d6e90fa38dec85e829f71018532ed5b709a50a585455fc07cb3bae282f5d1f

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-cairo >=1.5.9
    - r-ggbeeswarm
    - r-ggplot2 >=2.1.0
    - r-png
    - r-ragg
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-cairo >=1.5.9
    - r-ggbeeswarm
    - r-ggplot2 >=2.1.0
    - r-png
    - r-ragg

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('ggrastr')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('ggrastr')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/VPetukhov/ggrastr
  license: MIT
  summary: Provides a set of geoms to rasterize only specific layers of the plot while simultaneously keeping all labels and text in vector format. This allows users to keep plots within the reasonable size limit without loosing vector properties of the scale-sensitive information.
  license_family: MIT
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/MIT
    - LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r

# Package: ggrastr
# Type: Package

# Version: 0.2.1
